i## Generating HTTP Requests		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iAll SQL queries on InfluxDB are done over HTTP requests, so our STM32		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ionly needs to send a simple HTTP request. We can even disregard		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iwhatever data from the server.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> The main reason is that we are out of space on STM32's ROM, and		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i> cannot afford to add code to parse HTTP replies.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iHere is an example request:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i```bash		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iPOST /write?u=INFLUXUSER&p=INFLUXPASS&db=INFLUXDB HTTP/1.1\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iHost: influxdb.lantian.pub:8086\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iUser-Agent: lantian/2.3.3\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iContent-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iConnection: close\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iContent-Length: 26\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i\r\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
istm32_vref,id=1 value=3.5\n		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
